gest%20firms%20out%20there%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20revolving%20door%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20general%20partner%20Kevin%20Spain%2C%20who%20has%20been%20at%20Emergence%20for%2017%20years.%20%26quot%3BThat%20creates%20a%20lot%20of%20disruption%20and%20uncertainty%20for%20founders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmergence's%20response%20to%20that%20revolving%20door%20has%20been%20to%20carefully%20cultivate%20a%20distinct%20firm%20structure%2C%20from%20how%20it%20promotes%20partners%20to%20how%20it%20divides%20economics%20after%20a%20deal.%20Here's%20how%20it's%20approaching%20retention%20in%20an%20industry%20plagued%20by%20churn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cfae9d0f-9376-4f6b-96e5-1d077efefb3e%5C%22%3EEmergence's%20all-hands-on-deck%20strategy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20one%20of%20Emergence's%20six%20investing%20partners%2C%20Gordon%20Ritter%2C%20is%20a%20founder%20of%20the%20firm.%20Everyone%20else%20rose%20through%20the%20ranks%20over%20years%20of%20close%20collaboration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20associates%20have%20left%20the%20firm%20before%20reaching%20partner%20status.%20Other%20non-investing%20partners%2C%20such%20as%20Emergence's%20operating%20partners%2C%20have%20also%20come%20and%20gone.%20But%20when%20Emergence%20decides%20to%20make%20one%20of%20its%20investors%20a%20partner%2C%20they%20stick%20around%2C%20Spain%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20hand%20that%20title%20or%20those%20responsibilities%20out%20very%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20Spain%20said.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20we%20do%2C%20we%20know%20that%20person%20so%20well%20and%20they%20know%20us%20so%20well%20that%20it%20feels%20like%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do%2C%20and%20it%20feels%20like%20we%20are%20making%20a%20truly%20long-term%20commitment%20to%20one%20another.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223161%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Emergence%20Capital's%20team.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6866d3e285e81483682d6092%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222371%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEmergence%20Capital's%20team%2C%20including%20its%20seven%20investing%20partners%20and%20two%20non-investing%20partners.%3Cp%3EEmergence%20Capital%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20retention%20benefits%20Emergence's%20portfolio%20companies%20as%20well%2C%20Spain%20said.%20When%20a%20founder%20brings%20on%20an%20Emergence%20partner%20as%20a%20board%20member%2C%20they're%20less%20likely%20to%20face%20unexpected%20turnover%2C%20a%20common%20pain%20point%20in%20startup-investor%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20aims%20to%20invest%20with%20a%20high-confidence%2C%20low-volume%20strategy.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEach%20partner%20typically%20makes%20just%20one%20to%20two%20new%20investments%20per%20year%2C%20which%20Spain%20said%20also%20leads%20to%20more%20fulfilling%20work%20for%20the%20firm's%20investors%20since%20partners%20can%20go%20deep%20with%20the%20founders%20they%20bet%20on.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20spray%20and%20pray%2C%26quot%3B%20Spain%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20really%20invest%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20conviction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmergence%20has%20set%20up%20its%20diligence%20process%20to%20necessitate%20that%20kind%20of%20conviction%2C%20too%2C%20by%20requiring%20each%20partner%20to%20do%20their%20own%20primary%20research%20on%20every%20deal.%20Spain%20said%20that%20approach%20helps%20Emergence%20bring%20a%20wider%20range%20of%20complex%20perspectives%20to%20the%20table%20on%20investment%20decisions%2C%20while%20ensuring%20all%20of%20its%20investors%20have%20skin%20in%20the%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20end%2C%20when%20we're%20making%20an%20investment%20decision%2C%20it%20really%20feels%20like%20we're%20all%20owning%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Spain%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20setup%20is%20as%20it%20is%20at%20most%20venture%20firms%20%E2%80%94%20'I%20voted%20for%20your%20deal%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20really%20feel%20that%20strongly%20about%20it%20and%20now%20it's%20going%20sideways%3B%20that's%20on%20you%2C%20go%20figure%20it%20out'%E2%80%94%20that's%20not%20a%20great%20dynamic%2C%20either%20for%20the%20firm's%20culture%20or%20for%20ultimately%20coming%20up%20with%20solutions%20to%20the%20company's%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e22635c4-426f-4d88-b71e-1db0bcedcbf7%5C%22%3EThe%20deal%20that%20keeps%20partners%20around%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEmergence's%20returns%20help.%20The%20firm%20says%20it%20has%20generated%20more%20than%20%248%20billion%20in%20realized%20gains%20on%20less%20than%20%242%20billion%20invested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20work%20hard%20if%20you%20want%20to%20win%2C%26quot%3B%20Spain%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20great%20to%20put%20the%20work%20in%20and%20see%20it%20pay%20off.%20If%20you%20don't%20have%20that%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20anything%20else%20is%20going%20to%20matter%20quite%20as%20much.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20returns%20for%20limited%20partners%20don't%20tell%20the%20full%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpain%20remembers%20receiving%20an%20internal%20employee%20survey%20during%20his%20time%20in%20the%20early%202000s%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20where%20he%20helped%20manage%20the%20tech%20giant's%20acquisitions%20and%20investments.%20A%20single%20question%20on%20the%20survey%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20strong%20predictor%20of%20whether%20an%20employee%20would%20stay%20at%20Microsoft%3A%20%26quot%3Bhow%20would%20you%20rate%20the%20deal%20you're%20getting%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpain%20thinks%20the%20same%20premise%20applies%20to%20venture%20capital.%20At%20some%20firms%2C%20the%20economics%20are%20opaque%20and%20tilted%20toward%20founding%20partners%2C%20he%20said.%20Rising%20stars%20may%20put%20the%20work%20in%20but%20still%20not%20see%20a%20clear%20path%20forward%20for%20their%20ability%20to%20climb%20the%20ranks%20or%20to%20access%20compensation%20that%20feels%20fair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20feel%20like%20you%20are%20a%20star%20performer%20and%20you're%20putting%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20in%2C%20and%20what%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20in%20return%20is%20unclear%2C%20that's%20when%20the%20deal%20starts%20looking%20not%20so%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20Spain%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Spain%20didn't%20share%20details%20about%20Emergence's%20compensation%20structures%2C%20he%20said%20the%20firm%20takes%20an%20%26quot%3Begalitarian%26quot%3B%20approach%20to%20distributing%20wealth%2C%20allowing%20partners%20to%20share%20the%20economics%20%26quot%3Bin%20an%20equal%20way%26quot%3B%20as%20they%20move%20up%20in%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20acknowledged%20that%20not%20every%20firm%20should%20look%20like%20Emergence.%20The%20firm's%20smaller%20partnership%20and%20collaborative%20investment%20strategies%20could%20lend%20themselves%20more%20easily%20to%20transparent%20wealth%20distribution%2C%20conditions%20not%20every%20firm%20is%20set%20up%20to%20replicate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Spain%20worries%20that%20some%20VC%20firms%20with%20top-heavy%20structures%20are%20starting%20to%20show%20cracks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGreat%20people%20aren't%20always%20taken%20care%20of%2C%26quot%3B%20Spain%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20clear%20road%20map%2C%20particularly%20for%20the%20best%20performers.%20That%20gets%20people%20looking%2C%20or%20it%20dissuades%20them%20from%20staying%20in%20venture%20altogether.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvc-emergence-capital-hasnt-lost-partner-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752051602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6866d34085e81483682d6065%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvc-emergence-capital-hasnt-lost-partner-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20VC%20industry%20struggles%20with%20a%20revolving%20door%20of%20talent%2C%20Emergenc