t%20in%202021%20and%202022%2C%20college-educated%20fathers%20of%20children%20under%2018%20were%2C%20on%20average%2C%20spending%2010%20hours%20and%2012%20minutes%20a%20week%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-excited-free-time-kids-out-the-house-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewith%20their%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20over%20two%20hours%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20prior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20frequently%2C%20reality%20hasn't%20aligned%20with%20expectations.%20Many%20fathers%20say%20the%20stress%20and%20expectations%20that%20come%20with%20their%20job%20often%20take%20precedence%20over%20the%20care%20work%20that%20comes%20with%20having%20a%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20talk%20about%20the%20double%20shift%2C%20we%20often%20talk%20about%20women%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Richard%20Reeves%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%20who's%20also%20the%20president%20of%20the%20nonprofit%20American%20Institute%20for%20Boys%20and%20Men.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20don't%20talk%20about%20enough%20is%20that%20it's%20true%20of%20men%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20back%20as%202015%2C%20a%20New%20York%20Times%20headline%20declared%20that%20%26quot%3BMillennial%20Men%20Aren't%20the%20Dads%20They%20Thought%20They'd%20Be%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that's%20exactly%20what%20Scott%2C%20a%2039-year-old%20living%20on%20the%20West%20Coast%20who%20has%20a%203-year-old%20son%20and%20works%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-memo-big-tech-ai-win-court-rulings-data-copyright-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBig%20Tech%3C%2Fa%3E%20company%2C%20tells%20me%20he's%20found.%20%26quot%3BI%20really%20thought%20that%20I'd%20be%20able%20to%20create%20boundaries%20and%20draw%20lines%2C%20but%20it's%20really%20hard%2C%20especially%20in%20an%20industry%20like%20tech%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20the%20standards%20to%20which%20workers%20are%20held%20are%20just%20incompatible%20with%20wanting%20to%20be%20a%20really%20present%20parent%2C%20and%20that's%20especially%20true%20for%20dads.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202016%20paper%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Paradox%20of%20Today's%20Fathers%26quot%3B%20from%20Boston%20College's%20Center%20for%20Work%20and%20Family%20also%20speaks%20to%20this.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20clear%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote%2C%20that%20most%20young%20men%20face%20a%20%26quot%3Bconflict%20in%20trying%20to%20rectify%20their%20desire%20to%20be%20engaged%20fathers%20and%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20their%20children%20and%20their%20desire%20to%20'climb%20the%20corporate%20ladder'%20%E2%80%94%20advancing%20in%20the%20organization%2C%20seeking%20jobs%20with%20greater%20responsibility%2C%20and%20pursuing%20a%20career%20in%20senior%20management.%26quot%3B%20The%20result%20of%20all%20of%20this%2C%20they%20concluded%2C%20was%20the%20same%20dilemma%20that%20women%20had%20faced%20for%20years%3A%20%26quot%3BCan%20one%20really%20'%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwanted-to-be-young-mom-had-kids-later-in-life-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehave%20it%20all%3C%2Fa%3E%3F'%26quot%3B%20The%20response%20to%20that%20question%20for%20many%20dads%20seems%20pretty%20unequivocal%3A%20Absolutely%20not.%20Or%20at%20least%20not%20all%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%2041-year-old%20dad%20who%20works%20in%20consulting%20says%20that%20despite%20him%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20an%20accountant%2C%20explicitly%20agreeing%20before%20they%20had%20their%20daughter%20two%20years%20ago%20that%20they%20were%20going%20to%20try%20as%20hard%20as%20possible%20to%20split%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-paid-over-fifty-thousand-dollars-for-childcare-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echildcare%20responsibilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20equally%2C%20it%20didn't%20work.%20%26quot%3BMy%20wife%20took%20five%20months%20off%20work.%20I%20took%20two%20weeks%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat%20established%20a%20sort%20of%20default%3A%20She's%20the%20primary%20parent%2C%20and%20I'm%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20frustrating%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20really%20hard%20to%20change%2C%20especially%20because%20I'm%20constantly%20traveling%20for%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReeves%20agrees%20that%20defaults%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20change%20once%20they're%20set%20during%20those%20early%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%20advocates%20deliberately%20challenging%20them.%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20critical%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20that%20you%20can't%20allow%20the%20gender%20division%20to%20get%20solidified.%20It%20can't%20get%20set%20in%20stone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EJessica%20Calarco%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20sociology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Wisconsin%20Madison%20whose%20research%20focuses%20on%20inequalities%20in%20family%20structures%2C%20says%20the%20disconnect%20between%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-of-millennial-retirement-panic-boomer-parents-saving-401k-market-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20millennial%20dads'%20intention%20and%20realit%3C%2Fa%3Ey%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20two%20things%3A%20%26quot%3BA%20mismatch%20of%20socialization%20and%20a%20mismatch%20in%20structure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20society%2C%20we%20haven't%20socialized%20fathers%20to%20be%20caregivers%2C%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20only%20allowed%20gender%20to%20bend%20one%20way.%20We've%20told%20young%20girls%20they%20can%20be%20anything%20they%20want%20to%20be.%20But%20we're%20not%20encouraging%20boys%20to%20embrace%20care%20identities.%20We're%20not%20giving%20them%20baby%20boys%20dolls%20and%20tea%20sets.%26quot%3B%20As%20a%20result%2C%20%26quot%3Bdads%20can%20feel%20underprepared%20or%20crowded%20out%2C%20like%20they%20don't%20belong%20in%20caring%20roles.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20allowed%20women%20to%20do%20as%20much%20as%20men%2C%26quot%3B%20Chung%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20we%20have%20not%20allowed%20fathers%20to%20be%20as%20involved%20in%20childcare%20as%20women%20have%20been.%26quot%3B%20James%20Millar%2C%20a%20coauthor%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BDads%20Don't%20Babysit%2C%26quot%3B%20explains%20it%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeing-sole-breadwinner-family-important-lessons-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebreadwinner%3C%2Fa%3E%20stereotype%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20he%20says%20has%20made%20it%20so%20that%20%26quot%3Beven%20men%20who%20act%20on%20their%20desire%20to%20have%20a%20more%20equitable%20relationship%20are%20likely%20to%20suffer%20greater%20dissatisfaction%20if%20they%20are%20not%20the%20breadwinner%20in%20a%20couple%20or%20family.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJonas%20Rave%2C%20a%2040-year-old%20dad%20of%20one%20living%20in%20London%2C%20says%20he%20thinks%20gender%20stereotypes%20are%20particularly%20salient%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20language%20we%20tend%20to%20use.%20Words%20like%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-booking-app-bumo-raised-10-million-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecaregiving%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bnurturing%26quot%3B%20are%20%26quot%3Bdeeply%20feminine-coded%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20as%20a%20result%2C%20many%20men%20might%20feel%20less%20'manly'%20when%20they%20are%20'lead%20parent.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20traditional%20father%20who%20goes%20fishing%2C%20plays%20catch%2C%20coaches%20Little%20League%2C%20and%20suchlike%20is%20more%20societally%20acceptable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%20%26quot%3BThe%20emotionally%20available%2C%20more%20soft%20and%20gentle%20dad%2C%20possibly%20less%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20prospect%20of%20speaking%20about%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20these%20social%20pressures%20and%20entrenched%20stereotypes%20are%20challenging%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20harming%20%E2%80%94%20men%2C%20many%20of%20the%20people%20I%20interviewed%20didn't%20want%20to%20do%20so%20because%20they%20were%20scared%20of%20how%20they%20might%20be%20perceived.%20Some%20feared%20an%20employer%20might%20consider%20them%20less%20capable%20or%20committed%20to%20work%20if%20they%20acknowledged%20struggling%20with%20the%20parenthood%20juggle.%20Others%20didn't%20want%20to%20risk%20being%20seen%20to%20be%20complaining%20about%20something%20that%20mothers%20have%20endured%20for%20centuries.%20%26quot%3BThe%20last%20thing%20I'd%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20father%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20for%20anyone%20to%20think%20I'm%20'mansplaining'%20what%20women%20have%20been%20dealing%20with%20forever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mismatch%20in%20structure%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20evident%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20in%20countries%20such%20as%20the%20US%2C%20caregiving%20is%20not%20treated%20as%20a%20public%20utility%2C%20Calarco%20says.%20Instead%2C%20it's%20usually%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20enduring%20gender%20pay%20gap%2C%20which%20still%20sits%20at%20about%20%240.15%2C%20it's%20usually%20the%20woman%20who%20shoulders%20most%20of%20the%20burden%20of%20care.%20Of%20the%20countless%20families%20she's%20studied%20during%20her%20career%2C%20Calarco%20says%20she's%20only%20really%20witnessed%20egalitarian%20%E2%80%94%20or%20near-egalitarian%20%E2%80%94%20parenting%20arrangements%20in%20families%20that%20can%20afford%20to%20outsource%20almost%20all%20of%20the%20childcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorporate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-dont-take-all-parental-leave-because-of-corporate-bias-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eparental%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20also%20rarely%20gender%20equal%2C%20and%20though%20many%20companies%20have%20recently%20bolstered%20their%20paternity%20benefits%2C%20few%20offer%20all%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20regardless%20of%20gender%20%E2%80%94%20identical%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freasons-small-businesses-invest-paid-parental-leave-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleave%20and%20pay%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20cases%20in%20which%20it%20is%20offered%2C%20take-up%20is%20also%20often%20lackluster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20report%20published%20by%20McKinsey%20and%20the%20gender-equality%20nonprofit%20Moms%20First%20earlier%20this%20year%20found%20that%20dads%20in%20New%20York%20state%20were%20forgoing%20%241.6%20billion%20in%20state-guaranteed%20parental%20benefits%20by%20not%20taking%20leave.%20In%202021%2C%20an%20academic%20paper%20found%20that%20US%20fathers%20who%20did%20take%20parental%20leave%20typically%20took%20a%20week%20or%20less.%20That%20same%20paper%20also%20found%20that%20of%20those%20who%20did%20take%20leave%2C%20just%2014%25%20of%20fathers%20took%20more%20than%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20many%20of%20the%20dads%20I%20interviewed%20said%20they%20still%20thought%20men%20were%20judged%20for%20taking%20parental%20leave%20or%20assuming%20the%20role%20of%20primary%20caregiver.%20About%20a%20third%20of%20those%20I%20spoke%20with%20said%20that%20they%20didn't%20take%20all%20of%20the%20leave%20that%20they%20were%20legally%20entitled%20to.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20that%2C%20generally%20speaking%2C%20requests%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-hybrid-jobs-rto-jpmorgan-amazon-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ework%20flexibly%20or%20remotely%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20looked%20upon%20more%20favorably%20if%20they're%20made%20by%20women%20than%20by%20men%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Matt%20Fleischer%2C%20a%2041-year-old%20father%20of%20two%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20This%20effect%20is%20what%20Chung%20identifies%20as%20%26quot%3Bfemininity%20stigma%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20men%20being%20stigmatized%20or%20even%20punished%20for%20demanding%20certain%20accommodations%20and%20benefits%20that%20have%20historically%20been%20used%20by%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20overarching%20problem%20here%20is%20the%20inability%20of%20the%20labor%20market%20and%20society%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20new%20reality%20of%20parenting%20and%20work%20and%20evolving%20gender%20roles%20and%20norms%2C%26quot%3B%20Chung%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20labor%20market%20still%20demands%20so%20much%20of%20workers%20and%20especially%20male%20workers%20in%20male-dominated%20industries%2C%20and%20that's%20hurting%20us%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20the%20dads%20nor%20the%20academics%20I%20talked%20to%20were%20optimistic%20about%20being%20able%20to%20strike%20a%20balance%20soon.%20Calarco%20notes%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20cuts%20to%20certain%20services%20have%20eroded%20an%20already%20inadequate%20safety%20net%20that%20the%20government%20had%20up%20until%20recently%20provided.%20She%20says%20she's%20seeing%20a%20%26quot%3Bbacklash%20against%20anything%20that's%20not%20normative%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20while%20this%20is%20particularly%20pronounced%20in%20the%20US%20right%20now%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20US%20tends%20to%20be%20the%20canary%20in%20the%20coal%20mine%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20negative%20social%20change.%26quot%3B%20A%20push%20for%20%26quot%3Bhardcore%26quot%3B%20masculinity%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20touted%20by%20the%20likes%20of%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-america-party-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20Elon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20exacerbating%20an%20already%20deeply%20ingrained%20culture%20of%20presenteeism%20%E2%80%94%20is%20not%20helping%20either%2C%20several%20of%20the%20people%20I%20spoke%20to%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChung%20says%20it's%20still%20very%20much%20the%20case%20that%20employees%20who%20are%20pursuing%20the%20%26quot%3Bideal%20worker%20norm%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20embodied%20by%20someone%20who%20puts%20in%20extremely%20long%20hours%20and%20is%20myopically%20focused%20on%20their%20job%20%E2%80%94%20are%20rewarded%20the%20most%20generously.%20This%2C%20she%20says%2C%20creates%20incentive%20structures%20that%20don't%20allow%20for%20the%20workforce%20to%20evolve%20and%20to%20be%20more%20accommodating%20of%20parents.%20In%202023%2C%20Claudia%20Goldin%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20Harvard%2C%20won%20the%20Nobel%20Memorial%20Prize%20for%20her%20work%20highlighting%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20what%20Chung%20is%20referring%20to%3A%20the%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Bgreedy%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20employers%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-pivot-college-degrees-work-blue-collar-jobs-trades-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecertain%20industries%3C%2Fa%3E%20demand%20long%20hours%20and%20reward%20mostly%20male%20workers%20who%20are%20unencumbered%20by%20duties%20outside%20their%20paid%20jobs%2C%20such%20as%20parenting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20gender%20norms%20that%20are%20making%20it%20hard%20for%20dads%20and%20moms%20to%20be%20treated%20equally%20in%20work%20and%20in%20society%20are%20so%2C%20so%20deeply%20ingrained%20that%20I%20don't%20see%20things%20changing%20anytime%20soon%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Scott%2C%20the%20father%20of%20one%20from%20the%20West%20Coast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20really%20wish%20for%2C%20is%20for%20parenting%20to%20be%20widely%20seen%20as%20a%20path%20for%20personal%20growth%2C%20joyfulness%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20the%20stress%2C%20anxiety%2C%20boredom%2C%20and%20frustration%20%E2%80%94%20for%20both%20genders%20in%20different%20ways%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Rave%2C%20the%20dad%20in%20London%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20with%20the%20same%20ultimate%20goal%20in%20mind%3A%20to%20raise%20good%20humans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20that%20could%20move%20the%20needle%20is%20more%20role%20models.%20%26quot%3BNorms%20can%20shift%20quite%20quickly%20once%20you%20get%20a%20critical%20mass%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20